{"id": "EUVD-2024-2653", "enisaUuid": "b1877b9f-4b73-33fb-833f-69b01d4a03bc", "description": "Hono is a Web application framework that provides support for any JavaScript runtime. Hono CSRF middleware can be bypassed using crafted Content-Type header. MIME types are case insensitive, but isRequestedByFormElementRe only matches lower-case. As a result, attacker can bypass csrf middleware using upper-case form-like MIME type. This vulnerability is fixed in 4.5.8.", "datePublished": "2024-08-22T14:23:44", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-22T15:40:32", "baseScore": 5.0, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L", "references": ["https://github.com/honojs/hono/security/advisories/GHSA-rpfr-3m35-5vx5", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-43787", "https://github.com/honojs/hono/commit/41ce840379516410dee60c783142e05bb5a22449", "https://github.com/honojs/hono", "https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/b0af71fbcc6dbe44140ea76f16d68dfdb32a99a0/src/middleware/csrf/index.ts#L16-L17"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-43787", "GHSA-rpfr-3m35-5vx5"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "334b31f4-6538-312e-84c5-a8d414a487ff", "product": {"name": "hono"}, "product_version": "< 4.5.8"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "9480e712-d441-32f7-ae4f-e470ca63aa72", "vendor": {"name": "honojs"}}], "isExploited": false}